column1: Facilities with Publicly Reported Coronavirus Cases

Thousands of deaths from the coronavirus have been linked to nursing homes in recent weeks, but the federal government and many states have not identified the providers. Through media accounts and state health departments, The Post was able to identify more than 2,500 nursing homes that have had publicly reported cases of the virus among residents or staff as of Monday morning.

Note: With many states not releasing the names of facilities, the actual number of nursing homes impacted by the virus is likely far higher.
